The paper deals with computer vision and graphics, specifically 3D facial expression reconstruction from a single image. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of 3D models, which falls under cs.GR (Computer Graphics). Additionally, the paper uses a combination of features and a regression framework, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also discusses the robustness of the proposed method to expression and pose changes, which could be relevant to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques, which could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
